<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,706,1172]" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,263,1066,1092]" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">Note.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Dietrich &amp; Dmitriev" authorityYear="2006" box="[562,751,1066,1091]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Neozygina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadricornis">
<emphasis box="[562,751,1066,1091]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">N. quadricornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
externally, but differs in having the aedeagal shaft very slender and lacking distal processes. The specific name refers to the country where the 
<typeStatus box="[1200,1250,1106,1132]" pageId="8" pageNumber="35">type</typeStatus>
series was collected.
</paragraph>
